author: nutgaard
message:
fjernet tellerId fra textarea sitt aria-describedby

telleren er by-default en live-region pga `aria-live` attributte. aria-describedby gjorde derfor at teller-tekster ble lest opp dobbelt.

Flyttet id-generering ut av render-metoden slik at disse ikke gjenskapes ved hver render og skaper un√∏dvendig dom-oppdateringer.

author: erlendev
message:
Update package-lock, fix modules

Due to a bug / strange behaviour from one of our dependencies (react-docgen-typescript)
used to generate docgenInfo for components, in how it assigns displayName to components,
components used directly by the Guideline-app needs to be exported as classes instead of
as function constants / StatelessComponents after updating outdated package-lock.json
file.

Ref open issue in react-docgen-typescript:
https://github.com/styleguidist/react-docgen-typescript/issues/82

author: nutgaard
message:
Fjernet feil i Tekstomr√•de

Alle bruksm√∏nstre for `Tekstomr√•de` ga feil i consolen, da det
ble brukt `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` p√• en `Normaltekst` som forventer
`children`. Dette var n√∏dvendig pga konverteringen til lenker.

Vi parser n√• heller teksten selv, og generer react-komponenter (span/a)
for de ulike fragmentene vi finner.

Fjernet `sanitize-html` som avhengighet da den ikke er n√∏dvendig mer.

author: it-vegard
message:
Bugfix/dropdown voice over bug (#2303)

* Remove tabIndex="-1" for Popover component, to fix VoiceOver bug where navigation inside the Popover doesn't work.

This affects Datepicker, Dropdown, Timeline and the Popover components, but appears to cause no bugs.

Ref: https://nav-it.slack.com/archives/C7NE7A8UF/p1694158816166729

* Add changeset

* Might not be the best way, but it works. getFloatingProps added it's own tabIndex="-1", which we need to get rid of.

* Seems like getFloatingProps can take "tabIndex: undefined" as an option, reducing the amount of code we need to change.

author: it-vegard
message:
Add new useVirtualFocus hook, for use in Combobox (#2394)

* Add new useVirtualFocus hook, for use in Combobox. Might be useful for other components later, but will scope it for Combobox at first.

* Create filteredOptionsUtils, which has utiltity functions for creating IDs and for text lookups in lists.

* Get rid of data-value, and use filteredOptionsMap to look up the value of the currently (virtually) focused element instead

This allows use of e.g. numbers as options, which data-value didn't.

* Using useState instead of useRef to handle filteredOptionsRef

* Added changeset

* Force option id to be lower case, to avoid different casing from being interpreted as being different from the existing options

* Fix bug where it was not possible to select multiple custom (new) options in a multiselect

selectedOptionsContext is not available inside customOptionsContext, so need to take isMultiSelect from props instead

* Switch to use toLocalLowerCase and remove uneccessary use of string literal

* type mismatch

* Clean up types - reuse from ComboboxProps type definition, and fix resulting type mismatches

* Rename filteredOptionsRef variable returned from filteredOptionsContext to reflect that it is now actually a setState-function

* Expose virtualFocus as an object through filteredOptionsContext, instead of each separate method.

Done to remove need to wrap moveFocusUp and moveFocusDown in order to toggle isListOpen

- Velg mellom SingleSelect eller MultiSelect-versjon for henholdsvis ett og flere valg.

author: nutgaard
message:
Bruker less import-reference

Flere som har opplevd duplikat-styling n√•r man har brukt webpack og less-loader.
Dette skyldes at `nav-frontend-core` og `nav-frontend-typografi` blir importert
i stortsett alle modulene, og at less-loader kompilerer hver enkelt `require`
i sitt eget scope. S√• det er derfor ikke mulig √• oppdage duplikater vha plugins etc.

`@import (reference)` endrer p√• dette, slik at hver modul ikke drar med seg for mye styling.
Downside er at hvert prosjekt m√• i st√∏rre grad passe p√• at stylingen fra `nav-frontend-core` og
`nav-frontend-typografi` har blitt riktig lastet inn.

Dokumentasjonen til LESS:
> Use @import (reference) to import external files, but without adding the imported styles to the compiled output unless referenced.
http://lesscss.org/features/

author: it-vegard
message:
Bugfix/combobox bugfixes and tweaks (#2144)

* Clear input field when clicking option in multiselect combobox

Makes the behaviour consistent when clicking with a mouse and when selecting an option with keyboard.

* MultiSelect with "add new" example should actually have the addnewValues prop set...

* Expose through onToggleSelected whether selected values in combobox are added by the user or not.

* Add the additional affordance of bold font-weight for selected options in combobox.

Done to account for screen magnifiers on screens that don't show the background color, where the checkmark is out-of-sight.

* Avoid "jumping" when selecting option in multiselect, stemming from the chips being slightly larger than the padding allowed for (equal to the width of the border)

* Added changeset and updated yarn.lock

* Do not use focus-visible inside fallback for when focus-visible is not supported

* Add fallback focus-styling using JS and a helper class for browsers not supporting :has (Firefox)

* Fix for onBlur in ComboboxWrapper. Without tabindex="-1" event.relatedTarget in onBlur will be null, and we can't check that focus has entirely moved outside the Combobox.

author: it-vegard
message:
Autocomplete should keep upper-/lowercase from the word being autocompleted (#2207)

* AutoComplete should keep upper-/lowercase from the word being autocompleted

* Fix issue where autocomplete doesn't format the casing of the last character in the word

* Added changeset

* Append the autocompleted text in the same casing used in the list, but preserve casing for the typed characters

* Preserve casing used while typing, then use the casing from the options when selecting a value

* Added custom options to test of casing when typing

* Correct changeset

* When allowNewValues is enabled, we should use the new value as is when pressing Enter, instead of using the first FilteredOption

* Change test case to use a partial match for a word in options. This tests both that we will use "add new" option if available and that we preserve casing for new options

author: erlendev
message:
Export props from nav-frontend-skjema

A previous rewrite of nav-frontend-skjema did not include exports of
prop-interfaces specific to the skjema-components. This commit makes
sure to export those props out of index.tsx, to avoid having to specify
e.g. "nav-frontend-skjema/lib/radio-panel-gruppe" when importing those interfaces.

This commit also renames the interface exported from BekreftCheckboksPanel-module
from Props to BekreftCheckboksPanelProps.
